<glossary>
<definition id="fs-idp153776448">
<term>circuit</term>
<meaning id="fs-idp84330816">path taken by a current as it flows because of an electrical potential difference</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-idp101247744">
<term>current</term>
<meaning id="fs-idp26963360">flow of electrical charge; the SI unit of charge is the coulomb (C) and current is measured in amperes <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mtext>1 A</m:mtext><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:mfrac><m:mtext>C</m:mtext><m:mtext>s</m:mtext></m:mfrac></m:mrow><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math></meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-idp85536816">
<term>electrical potential</term>
<meaning id="fs-idp213355216">energy per charge; in electrochemical systems, it depends on the way the charges are distributed within the system; the SI unit of electrical potential is the volt <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mtext>1 V</m:mtext><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:mfrac><m:mtext>J</m:mtext><m:mtext>C</m:mtext></m:mfrac></m:mrow><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math></meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-idp62148528">
<term>half-reaction method</term>
<meaning id="fs-idp50666320">method that produces a balanced overall oxidation-reduction reaction by splitting the reaction into an oxidation “half” and reduction “half,” balancing the two half-reactions, and then combining the oxidation half-reaction and reduction half-reaction in such a way that the number of electrons generated by the oxidation is exactly canceled by the number of electrons required by the reduction</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-idp110333904">
<term>oxidation half-reaction</term>
<meaning id="fs-idp124211088">the “half” of an oxidation-reduction reaction involving oxidation; the half-reaction in which electrons appear as products; balanced when each atom type, as well as the charge, is balanced</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-idp21459792">
<term>reduction half-reaction</term>
<meaning id="fs-idp268683040">the “half” of an oxidation-reduction reaction involving reduction; the half-reaction in which electrons appear as reactants; balanced when each atom type, as well as the charge, is balanced
</meaning>
</definition>
</glossary>
